once a day
Homonym Number:
Word Class:phrase
Sense Number: 1
Definition:[dairying] milking cows once daily before drying off or to restrict milking to once daily for animal husbandry reasons.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes:
Citations
Date: 4/4/2001
Source: Fencepost.com
Author:
Vol / Page: Expert Farming
Edition:
Quote: Traditionally the shift to once a day is generally used as a signal to the herd that drying off time is not too far off. The expectation is that once a day will initiate a reduction in milk production. However, there is also the obvious positive side to once a day. Once a day will increase cow condition (or decrease condition loss.)
Notes:

